
Function: ZILFLAT

Syntax:   (ZILFLAT arg1 arg2)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - any LISP object.
 arg2 (required, evaluated) - T or NIL.

Returns:

 An integer containing the number of characters required to print
 out the represention of arg1 (via PRINC if arg2 is NIL, via PRIN1
 if arg2 is T).

Processing:

 The number of character positions taken up by the printed format
 of the object is returned as the value.

Errors signaled:

 None.

Notes:

 ZILFLAT is the internal ZIL function that underlies FLATC and
 FLATSIZE.

